 <H1>Issues in Index Selection (Contd.)</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Multi-attribute search keys should be considered when a WHERE clause contains several conditions.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>If range selections are involved, order of attributes should be carefully chosen to match the range ordering.
<LI>Such indexes can sometimes enable index-only strategies for important queries.
<UL></P>

<P><LI>For index-only strategies, clustering is not important!
</UL></UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>When considering a join condition:
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Hash index on inner is very good for Index Nested Loops.
<UL></P>

<P><LI>Should be clustered if join column is not key for inner, and inner tuples need to be retrieved.
</UL><LI>Clustered B+ tree on join column(s) good for Sort-Merge.</UL></UL></P>

<P></P> 
